Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Bush's first week and 'African-Americans'
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00ydtlw
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 20 Jan 1989
President Bush's failure to recall the date of the Pearl Harbour attack, and Reverend Jessie Jackson's attempt to instigate the use of the term 'African American'.